{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"deck-golem-scuff","description":"## Why\n\nThe cross-cutting requirement is ONE shared registry consumed by all gates. The risky core is\nalready shared (`review_kernel/` verify/decide/coach â€” both gates consume it). But the\nregistry/descriptor layer is duplicated: plan-review has `load_criteria()` (a merged descriptor);\ncode-review (`b744`) has only `routing_index()` (raw routing, no descriptor loader, no\n`facet/checklist`, and a **deliberately divergent** `blocking_enabled` vs `default_posture`). This\nstory unifies them into `rebar.llm.criteria`. **Blocked on `b744` landing** (WS1â€“WS5 committed on\n`worktree-code-review-capability`; WS6 = Gerrit voter pending) â€” so it is the post-b744 capstone;\nstories `#1`â€“`#5` proceed on plan-review without it.\n\n## What\n\n- Introduce `rebar.llm.criteria`: the shared merged-descriptor abstraction + loader both gates\n  consume (generalize plan-review's `load_criteria`; give code-review the descriptor it lacks).\n- Reconcile the **deliberate** posture divergence in one `threshold_for` that honors BOTH\n  `default_posture` (plan-review) and `blocking_enabled` (code-review) â€” do NOT \"fix\" the\n  divergence away.\n- Exec-tier-polymorphic criteria: LLM overlays (prompt+contract+routing) AND prompt-less DET\n  invariants (the 2 security keys live only in code-review's `criteria_routing.json` today).\n- Route code-review's `OVERLAY_IDS` / `routing_index` / `threshold_for` through the shared\n  `effective_criteria` so code-review also gets project criteria + the `.rebar/` overlay.\n- **Preserve `review_code` / `code_review/shim.py`'s `review_result` return shape** â€” a\n  back-compat surface consumed by MCP `review_code`, CLI `rebar review-code`, and the Gerrit\n  `review_bot/adapter.py`.\n- Port `plan_review/attest.py` to code-review (code-review signs nothing today) so its attestations\n  are kind-keyed + carry a code-review `registry_version` (completes story `#4` cross-gate).\n- Docs/ADR: the how-to for authoring/activating/eval'ing/blocking on a criterion across gates.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Files: new `src/rebar/llm/criteria/` (shared); `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/registry.py` +\n  `code_review/registry.py` (delegate to it); `code_review/` attestation port.\n- Migration is expand-contract; rollback = fail-open to packaged (overlay absent â‡’ both gates\n  behave as today). A misbehaving unified registry falls back per-gate.\n- BLOCKED ON `b744` (epic `3156` already `depends_on b744`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A shared `rebar.llm.criteria` layer that both plan-review and code-review consume, replacing\n      the two parallel registries.\n- [ ] `threshold_for` honors BOTH posture conventions (`default_posture` + `blocking_enabled`)\n      without collapsing the divergence.\n- [ ] The shared descriptor is exec-tier-polymorphic (LLM overlay + prompt-less DET).\n- [ ] Code-review consumes `effective_criteria` (project criteria + `.rebar/` overlay work in\n      code-review too).\n- [ ] `review_code` / `shim.py` `review_result` return shape is preserved (MCP + CLI + Gerrit).\n- [ ] Code-review issues kind-keyed attestations via a ported `attest.py` with a code-review\n      `registry_version` (completes cross-gate story `#4`).\n- [ ] An ADR + `CLAUDE.md`/`docs/` how-to documents the unified registry across gates.","id":"5065-0192-cc5e-4d01","parent_id":"3156-9092-1967-4367","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Unify plan-review + code-review into shared rebar.llm.criteria (blocked on b744)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782872269911662001,"uuid":"93a011fa-69a0-4ed5-8fae-6e51db75e026"}